DTEND:20160419T040000Z
DTSTAMP:20260409T144146Z
UID:etg207fl8jo6h7o5b8qf05mevk@google.com
CREATED:20160405T174150Z
DESCRIPTION:http://www.cityarts.net/event/the-power-of-gaming-2/\n\nTHE POW
 ER OF GAMING\nJane McGonigal\nIn Conversation with Kishore Hari\nMonday\, A
 pril 18\, 2016\, 7:30 pm\nVenue: Nourse Theater\nJane McGonigal is the foun
 der of Future Forecaster and Director of Games Research & Development at th
 e Institute for the Future. A pioneer in the field of alternate reality gam
 ing\, McGonigal specializes in games that improve real lives and tackle rea
 l world problems. In her game Snow World\, players navigate an icy world wh
 ile engaging in a snowball fight. The impact? Burn victims experienced a de
 crease in pain by 30 percent just by playing the game. Some of her latest r
 esearch focuses on preventing traumatic events from forming into PTSD simpl
 y by having victims play video games. Her latest book\,Super Better\, draws
  a game map for a revolutionary approach to getting stronger\, happier\, br
 aver\, and more resilient. Jane McGonigal will be in conversation with Kish
 ore Hari\, a science educator and the Director of the Bay Area Science Fest
 ival.
LAST-MODIFIED:20160405T174228Z
LOCATION:Nourse Theatre\, 275 Hayes St\, San Francisco\, CA 94117\, United 
 States
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:The Power of Gaming Talk
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
