DTEND:20230921T030000Z
DTSTAMP:20260409T144146Z
UID:28u70u7l53k0ehl6odh0upg8q4@google.com
CREATED:20230823T033050Z
DESCRIPTION:Snack Guidelines\n\nThe following guidelines have been establis
 hed to help Pied Piper families provide healthy &\nnutritious snacks for th
 e children. We are a nut-free school.\n\nFood Preparation\n• Please wash ha
 nds with warm\, soapy water before handling food.\n• Wash fruits and vegeta
 bles thoroughly and cut at school or home.\n• Clean snack table just prior 
 to and after snack time with cleaner.\n• Food must be cut properly to avoid
  choking hazards (grapes\, carrots\, hot dogs\, etc.)\nHealthy Snacks & Dri
 nks\n• Be sure to check the food allergies listed on kitchen counter.\n• Pl
 ease avoid high sugar foods. (i.e.: doughnuts\, fruit roll-ups\, fruit snac
 ks\,\ncookies\, cupcakes\, etc.)\n• Choose minimally processed foods. Avoid
  prepackaged foods as they may\ncontain little natural food and be high in 
 fat\, salt or sugar.\n• Drinks may include: 100% juice\, milk or water (fil
 tered preferably).\n• Try to include a well balanced snack that includes a 
 protein\, whole grain and fruit\nand or vegetable.\nCreative Snack Ideas\nR
 aisins\, dried cranberries * Fruit kabobs * Vegetables & dip * Whole grain 
 crackers & cheese\n* Mini whole wheat bagels with cream cheese * Applesauce
  * sandwich quarters * Individual\npizzas * Apple wedges * Quesadillas * En
 glish muffins & low-sugar jam * Yogurt & fruit\nsmoothie with orange juice 
 * Bean dip & crackers * Cottage cheese with fruit * Berries &\ncheddar chee
 se cubes * Tortilla chips & bean dip or guacamole * Yogurt with fruit * Egg
 \nsandwiches * Cherry tomatoes & cheese * Whole grain granola\, yogurt & ba
 nanas * Turkey\n& cream cheese roll-ups * Mini turkey or ham sandwiches * W
 hole grain muffins (carrot\,\nzucchini\, pumpkin) * Hummus with flatbread o
 r carrots * Scrambled eggs & ham * Breakfast\nburritos * Whole wheat grille
 d cheese sandwiches\nFruits & Vegetables*\n\n31\n\nBananas - Cut into quart
 ers or halves with peel on for convenience\nApples and Pears – Sliced into 
 wedges\nMelons and Cantaloupe – Cubed or use a melon-baller for fun shapes\
 nBerries - Serve as is\nOranges – Wedges\nGrapes - Cut in quarters or halve
 s\nPlums\, Peaches and Nectarines - Pitted and cut in half Sugar Snap\nPeas
 \, Edamame – Serve as is\nBroccoli – Cut into small florets Cucumbers – Sli
 ced\nCherry tomatoes – Cut in half\, if large\n* If possible\, try to purch
 ase organic – especially apples\, bell peppers\, celery\, cherries\, import
 ed grapes\,\nnectarines\, peaches\, pears\, potatoes\, red raspberries\, sp
 inach\, and strawberries – as these contain the highest\namount of pesticid
 e residues (even after washing).\nBreads & Grains*\nWhole Grain Crackers or
  Pretzels\nWhole Wheat Breads\, Pita Bread\, Tortillas\nFruit or Vegetable 
 Muffins\, Granola Bars - Choose lower sugar\, whole grain versions\n● A goo
 d rule of thumb to know if breads are whole grain is if they have more than
  3 grams of fiber per\nserving or the whole grain is listed on the top of t
 he ingredient list (instead of flour)\nProtein Foods (Meat / Meat Alternate
 )*\nHard Boiled Eggs\, deviled eggs\, mini egg salad sandwiches Seeds &\nBu
 tters (soy butter on fruit\, veggies\, bread or crackers)\nBeans – bean dip
 s or hummus\nYogurt - lowfat\, low-sugar or plain with honey & fruit\nChees
 e - Slices of cheddar or American cheese\, string cheese\, cottage cheese\n
 * Try to find minimally processed deli meats that are lower in salt and are
  not preserved with sodium nitrate.
LAST-MODIFIED:20230823T033050Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Prep Pied Piper Snack!
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
