BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20251114
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20251115
DTSTAMP:20260409T144146Z
UID:7let7pn27kqt8o3j10salqg17i@google.com
CREATED:20251113T185625Z
DESCRIPTION:\nOn Friday morning\, we are going to have a special walk and b
 ike to school day. Why is this one special? Because it is a day where we ho
 nor Ruby Bridges who was a brave little girl who made history in 1960. When
  she was only six years old\, she became the first African American student
  to attend an all-white elementary school in New Orleans\, Louisiana. Every
  day\, she walked to school escorted by federal marshals to keep her safe a
 gainst the backlash she faced. \n\nRuby’s courage helped change our country
 . She showed that one person—even a child—can make a big difference by stan
 ding up for what is right. Today\, Ruby Bridges is remembered as a hero for
  fairness\, courage\, and equality. We hope you will walk with us if you ar
 e able. We also wear purple to show our support for Ruby!
LAST-MODIFIED:20251113T190016Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:🚶🏾‍♀️ Ruby Bridges walk to school day
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
